title: Mets-Nationals game postponed, doubleheader set for Saturday
text:
Mets-Nationals game postponed by rain, teams will play split doubleheader Saturday THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   4:29   4:29   
Organizations: 
New York (1742) 

NEW YORK â€” The New York Mets and Washington Nationals had their game Friday postponed by rain and they will play a day-night doubleheader Saturday. 
The first game will start at 1:10 p.m. and the nightcap at 7:10 p.m. 
The Mets went into the final weekend of the season at 89-70, tied with the Los Angeles Dodgers, who they will meet in the playoffs next week.
